During the 2016 Republican presidential primary, Mitt Romney warned that if Donald Trump were elected, the United States would cease being such a place.
Trump’s administration is using children as pawns in an effort to deter illegal immigration and asylum seeking.
A father took his own life after border agents forcibly took his 3-year-old son from his arms in Texas, the Washington Post reported.
It’s one thing to take a hardline approach to curbing illegal entry into the United States.
This is a crime against humanity – one that could only be carried out by a nation and a people who have become hardened by our own generational trauma.